Package mars.assembler

Class Directives

  • java.lang.Object
    • mars.assembler.Directives

  • public final class Directives
extends java.lang.Object
    Class representing RISCV assembler directives. If Java had enumerated types, these would probably be implemented that way. Each directive is represented by a unique object. The directive name is indicative of the directive it represents. For example, DATA represents the MIPS .data directive.
    Version:
    August 2003
    Author:
    Pete Sanderson

      • matchDirective

        public static Directives matchDirective​(java.lang.String str)
        Find Directive object, if any, which matches the given String.
        Parameters:
        str - A String containing candidate directive name (e.g. ".ascii")
        Returns:
        If match is found, returns matching Directives object, else returns null.

      • prefixMatchDirectives

        public static java.util.ArrayList prefixMatchDirectives​(java.lang.String str)
        Find Directive object, if any, which contains the given string as a prefix. For example, ".a" will match ".ascii", ".asciiz" and ".align"
        Parameters:
        str - A String
        Returns:
        If match is found, returns ArrayList of matching Directives objects, else returns null.
